sub_title: Data Migration Engineer | ETL Specialist | Full Stack Developer | Ruby on Rails | HTML | CSS |  Bootstrap | JavaScript ES6 | SQL | Git | GitHub | Heroku |
summary:
I just completed the 9-week intense Full-Stack Web Developer Bootcamp in Le Wagon. I started my journey as an Architect focusing mainly on families who needed to redesign their homes.  And thanks to this method I developed a strong sense of empathy for others and a user-centric approach to design. I learned how to efficiently interview the client to quickly understand their needs and desires, allowing the client to review many options before committing, saving time and resources. 

I found this to be a great starting point when I explored UX design and I quickly became passionate about  Web and Mobile App design. I have always enjoyed having the knowledge which allows me to be involved in all the stages of design and building of a product so I naturally transitioned toward Full-Stack Web Development. 

I'm looking forward to using these skills in a new position as a  Full-Stack Developer and working with a fun, creative, and innovative team.

Some of my interests are skating, drawing, patternmaking, and sailing.
